de.pifpafpuf.web.urlparam

Class UrlParam<TYPE>

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.pifpafpuf.web.urlparam.UrlParam<TYPE>
  • Type Parameters:
    TYPE - is the type of the parameter stored.

    public class UrlParam<TYPE>
extends Object

    describes a single value URL parameter of the given TYPE. Objects of this class are immutable, but may be used as builders for objects for the same TYPE but with another value. Objects of this type are used to fetch parameters from the ServletRequest as well as to write the parameter with its value into a URL or an HTML form element.

    Example use of an int parameter.

     // define the template
 private static final UrlParam P_COUNT =
    new UrlParam("count", 0, new IntegerCodec(0, 10));
 ...
 // read the value from the request, using the default if necessary
 int count = P_COUNT.getFirst(request).getValue();
 ...
 // create a new parameter value to put it into the response
 UrlParam newCount = P_COUNT.fromValue(9);
 newCount.appendToUrl(buf);
 ...
 new Html("input").setAttr("type", "text")
 .setAttr("name", newCount.getName())
 .setAttr("value", newCount.getForInputParam()));

    • Constructor Detail

      • UrlParam

        public UrlParam(String name,
        TYPE value,
        ParamCodec<TYPE> pp)
        creates a url parameter. Objects created with the constructor are supposed to be used as templates. They shall be used to create new UlrParam objects either with fromValue(TYPE) or with fromFirst(javax.servlet.ServletRequest).
        Parameters:
        name - of the parameter as used in the URL. No check is made whether the name conforms to the syntax rules of URL parameter names and no encoding/decoding is performed for the name.
        value - is the default value for this parameter and may be null to signal the complete absence of a the parameter. (Advice: Don't use null, rather use a good default value if at all possible.)
        pp - is the codec to decode strings retrieved from ServletRequest and to encode the value for a URL or an HTML form input element. The codec should only encode/decode to/from an arbitrary String URL en/decoding is taken care of separately.

        appends the encoded value of this to the StringBuilder provided. If the URL provided does not end with a '?', the parameter is prefixed with '&'.
